    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - Fog Lights - Install</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Fog Lights - Install</title>
        <para>With hood tilted insert the fog light assembly into the center opening of the front bumper and locate the
            mounting hole.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align and insert fog light assembly in mounting bracket. Install flat washer and lock nut,
                finger tighten. Adjust the fog light direction and tighten mounting bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900863">Figure 63, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900863" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900863.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Fog Light Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LENS COVER RETAINING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CROSS BAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. VERTICAL ADJUSTMENT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FRONT BUMPER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Plug fog light harness into headlight assembly harness.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
